<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFE._L._Glaser.2C_J._F._Couleur.2C_G._A._Oliver">E. L. Glaser, J. F. Couleur, G. A. Oliver. <a href="http://www.multicians.org/fjcc2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.multicians.org/fjcc2.html" rel="nofollow">"System Design of a Computer for Time Sharing Applications"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.multicians.org/fjcc2.html" class="external free" title="http://www.multicians.org/fjcc2.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.multicians.org/fjcc2.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=System+Design+of+a+Computer+for+Time+Sharing+Applications&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=E.+L.+Glaser%2C+J.+F.+Couleur%2C+G.+A.+Oliver&amp;rft.au=E.+L.+Glaser%2C+J.+F.+Couleur%2C+G.+A.+Oliver&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.multicians.org%2Ffjcc2.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Virtual_memory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFBensoussanClingen1972">Bensoussan, A.; Clingen, C. T. (May 1972), "<a href="http://www.multicians.org/multics-vm.html" class="external text" title="http://www.multicians.org/multics-vm.html" rel="nofollow">The Multics Virtual Memory: Concepts and Design</a>", <i>Communications of the ACM</i> <b>15</b> (5): 308–318, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1145%2F355602.361306" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1145%2F355602.361306" rel="nofollow">10.1145/355602.361306</a></span><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.multicians.org/multics-vm.html" class="external free" title="http://www.multicians.org/multics-vm.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.multicians.org/multics-vm.html</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=The+Multics+Virtual+Memory%3A+Concepts+and+Design&amp;rft.jtitle=Communications+of+the+ACM&amp;rft.aulast=Bensoussan&amp;rft.aufirst=A.&amp;rft.au=Bensoussan%2C+A.&amp;rft.au=Clingen%2C+C.+T.&amp;rft.date=May+1972&amp;rft.volume=15&amp;rft.issue=5&amp;rft.pages=308%E2%80%93318&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1145%2F355602.361306&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.multicians.org%2Fmultics-vm.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Virtual_memory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFOrganick1972">Organick, E.I. (1972), <i>The Multics System: An Examination of Its Structure</i>, MIT Press</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Multics+System%3A+An+Examination+of+Its+Structure&amp;rft.aulast=Organick&amp;rft.aufirst=E.I.&amp;rft.au=Organick%2C+E.I.&amp;rft.date=1972&amp;rft.pub=MIT+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Virtual_memory"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ol>
</div>
<ul>
<li>John L. Hennessy, David A. Patterson, <i>Computer Architecture, A Quantitative Approach</i> (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1558607242" class="internal">ISBN 1-55860-724-2</a>)</li>
<li>Virtual Memory Secrets by Murali</li>
</ul>
